<subSubSection id="B1AB9CAAEC51FF9EB1E3FE3BFA13F88C" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F90ECF21EC51FF9EB1E3FE3BFAEDFDBF" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,610]" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB1E3FE3BFED8FE0C" bold="true" box="[199,322,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Externally, the new species (Figs 1, 2) is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB259FE34FB93FE0C" authorityName="Wu &amp; Pan" authorityYear="2015" box="[893,1033,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bayizhena">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB259FE34FB93FE0C" box="[893,1033,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. bayizhena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 3) and 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB5B3FE34FB67FE0C" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2014" box="[1175,1277,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB5B3FE34FB67FE0C" box="[1175,1277,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 4), but it can be separated by the following morphological characters (character states for related species are parenthesized): in 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB191FD8CFECFFDC4" authority="Wu &amp; Zhao &amp; Han, 2022" authorityName="Wu &amp; Zhao &amp; Han" authorityYear="2022" box="[181,341,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medogensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB191FD8CFECFFDC4" box="[181,341,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. medogensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB078FE73FE2DFDC4" bold="true" box="[348,439,511,537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D0F6AE48EC51FF9EB078FE73FE2DFDC4" box="[348,439,511,537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, the forewing, thorax, and abdomen are densely diffused with silvery scales (in 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB462FD8CFF42FDE0" authorityName="Wu &amp; Pan" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bayizhena">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB462FD8CFF42FDE0" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. bayizhena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB037FDA8FEE1FDE0" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2014" box="[275,379,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB037FDA8FEE1FDE0" box="[275,379,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are without silvery scales on the body); the forewing without distinct rounded whitish spots along the postmedial line (in 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB0FBFDC4FDF6FDBC" authorityName="Wu &amp; Pan" authorityYear="2015" box="[479,620,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bayizhena">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB0FBFDC4FDF6FDBC" box="[479,620,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. bayizhena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB386FDC4FC93FDBC" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2014" box="[674,777,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB386FDC4FC93FDBC" box="[674,777,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the postmedial line consists of rounded whitish spots).
</paragraph>
<caption id="ADCE9FA9EC51FF9EB1B3FA78FB01F989" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552202" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6552202" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552202/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" startId="2.[151,264,1524,1548]" targetBox="[151,1435,633,1501]" targetPageId="2">
