</taxonomicName>
, male, Yunnan, China (in NEFU). Scale bar: 10 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="F90ECF21EC51FF9EB1E3F90FFAFAF938" blockId="2.[151,1437,1667,2017]" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">
The male genitalia of the new species (Figs 5, 6) are diagnostic. The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB5F0F908FAFBF940" authorityName="Wu &amp; Pan" authorityYear="2015" box="[1236,1377,1667,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bayizhena">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB5F0F908FAFBF940" box="[1236,1377,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. bayizhena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 7), 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB198F924FEBBF91C" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2014" box="[188,289,1703,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB198F924FEBBF91C" box="[188,289,1703,1729]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 8), and other congeners by the apex of uncus being blunt and the phallus strongly curved mesally; whereas in all congeners, the uncus is acute apically and the phallus is almost straight or only weakly curved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F90ECF21EC51FF9EB1E3F963FA13F88C" blockId="2.[151,1437,1667,2017]" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">
In the female genitalia, 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB0F6F97CFDEBF8D4" authority="Wu &amp; Zhao &amp; Han, 2022" authorityName="Wu &amp; Zhao &amp; Han" authorityYear="2022" box="[466,625,1775,1801]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medogensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB0F6F97CFDEBF8D4" box="[466,625,1775,1801]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. medogensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB35DF963FD49F8D4" bold="true" box="[633,723,1775,1801]" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D0F6AE48EC51FF9EB35DF963FD49F8D4" box="[633,723,1775,1801]" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(Fig. 9) is easily distinguished from the congeners with known female genitalia (
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB078F898FE55F8F0" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2014" box="[348,463,1811,1837]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erlanga">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB078F898FE55F8F0" box="[348,463,1811,1837]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. erlanga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB0F9F898FDD5F8F0" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2014" box="[477,591,1812,1837]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenta">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB0F9F898FDD5F8F0" box="[477,591,1812,1837]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. argenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB3AAF898FD5AF8F0" authorityName="Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[654,704,1811,1837]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lii">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB3AAF898FD5AF8F0" box="[654,704,1811,1837]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. lii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by the corpus bursae with a single star-shaped signum; whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB190F8B4FEBCF88C" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2014" box="[180,294,1847,1873]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erlanga">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB190F8B4FEBCF88C" box="[180,294,1847,1873]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. erlanga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB079F8B4FE54F88C" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2014" box="[349,462,1848,1873]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenta">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB079F8B4FE54F88C" box="[349,462,1848,1873]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. argenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the corpus bursae has a small area of stellate signa and in 
<taxonomicName id="3EB1B4A2EC51FF9EB547F8B4FB0CF88C" authorityName="Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[1123,1174,1847,1873]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudohampsonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lii">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC51FF9EB547F8B4FB0CF88C" box="[1123,1174,1847,1873]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="69">P. lii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the signum is absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B1AB9CAAEC51FF98B1E3F8D7FF5EFE54" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="71" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" type="description">
