<subSubSection id="B1AB9CAAEC57FF98B1E3FA48FDD8F9DF" pageId="4" pageNumber="71" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="F90ECF21EC57FF98B1E3FA48FDD8F9DF" blockId="4.[151,1436,1476,1539]" pageId="4" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="CBC51333EC57FF98B1E3FA48FED4FA03" bold="true" box="[199,334,1476,1502]" pageId="4" pageNumber="71">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named after the Tibetan name of its 
<typeStatus id="260A7183EC57FF98B2E9FA48FC67FA03" box="[973,1021,1476,1502]" pageId="4" pageNumber="71">type</typeStatus>
locality “Medog” County of 
<collectingRegion id="3B7501C3EC57FF98B46FFA48FA06FA03" box="[1355,1436,1476,1502]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="4" pageNumber="71">Xizang</collectingRegion>
Autonomous Region (= 
<collectingRegion id="3B7501C3EC57FF98B082FA64FE7FF9DE" box="[422,485,1512,1539]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="4" pageNumber="71">Tibet</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry id="81A68FB1EC57FF98B0DCFA64FDA5F9DF" box="[504,575,1512,1538]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="71">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
